TopicTitle: KSP Interstellar Extended Continued Development Thread

Articles.Content:
48 minutes ago, Ourworldalpha1 said:

I did 3 Times,

Its like Ksp interstellar doesn,t want to load for me since 0.90

and when it loads there is a load of glitches which makes it unplayable

my solution was to look for the dev version of rcssound and download it manually. worked fine after that

1 hour ago, Ourworldalpha1 said:

I did 3 Times,

Its like Ksp interstellar doesn,t want to load for me since 0.90

and when it loads there is a load of glitches which makes it unplayable

It's very important you unpack the WarpPlugin in the correct folder, otherwise you can get the problems you describe

Version 1.8.8 for Kerbal Space Program 1.1

Released on 2016-04-19

  • Updated IFS to 1.21 which fixes compatibility with KER / Mech Jeb
  • Updated RCSSounds which fixes issues with KSPI-E RCS
  • Updated Module Manager to 2.6.22
Edited April 19, 2016 by FreeThinker

so is this mod no longer on CKAN?  CKAN claims that it is not available for *any* version of KSP, at present.  Is this intentional?  Interstellar Fuel Switch is still up there (and updated for 1.1), but KSPIE is not.

1 hour ago, ss8913 said:

so is this mod no longer on CKAN?  CKAN claims that it is not available for *any* version of KSP, at present.  Is this intentional?  Interstellar Fuel Switch is still up there (and updated for 1.1), but KSPIE is not.

I think those configuration files need an update, I will take a look

After looking at the config file, the problem is that I'm not sure what to do. The problem is that KSP 1.1 is in a high state of flux, dependancies are either no longer compatible, avialble or stable.

I think it's probably best to wait until the official release and the dust has settled before I do some major changes on CKAN

Edited April 20, 2016 by FreeThinker

Edited April 20, 2016 by FreeThinker

if I delete RCS Sounds, will it affect/break my KSPI install in any other way?

I have a bug where the thrust animation is playing for all of my RCS thrusters, at all times, even inside the VAB, and I am trying to debug it. Deleting RCS Sounds fixes the problem, and a quick check on that mod's thread shows that KSPI probably doesn't depend on it for anything other than, well, rcs sounds, but I just wanted to make sure.

 

Just in the interest of completeness, deleting RCS Sounds didn't actually fix my bug. I'm not sure why I thought it did. Now that my post on this thread shows up on google for "rcs animation inside VAB" I figured I had better say so.

Edited April 20, 2016 by JohnWittle

27 minutes ago, JohnWittle said:

if I delete RCS Sounds, will it affect/break my KSPI install in any other way?

I have a bug where the thrust animation is playing for all of my RCS thrusters, at all times, even inside the VAB, and I am trying to debug it. Deleting RCS Sounds fixes the problem, and a quick check on that mod's thread shows that KSPI probably doesn't depend on it for anything other than, well, rcs sounds, but I just wanted to make sure.

From what I heard, it should work. At worst you will no longer hear any RCS sounds, however, this isn't necessary if you replaced it with the updated RCSSound folder bundeled with the KSPI-E 1.8.8 package

Just upgraded to 1.1, upgraded to KSPI 1.8.8 at the same time. I have a ship fueled by liquid fuel and with a closed cycle gas core engine. The engine's description still says it will use liquid fuel, but the engine on the ship flames out and says "LqdHydrogen deprived", and won't switch. Moreover in VAB when I cycle through fuel types it goes Helium-Lithium-Nitrogen-Argon-Xenon, Liquid Fuel and Hydrogen aren't options. The engine does correctly detect & burn hydrogen on the launch pad when attached to a hydrogen tank though (and the interface says Propellant: Hydrogen), but not when there's a liquid fuel or LFO tank attached. What's going on?
Are you in sandbox or career? It seems like you're using a unupgraded version of that engine.
I'm in science. Is the upgrade why is says both empty mass = 16 tons and empty mass = 20 tons in the VAB? I'm not seeing the upgrade in the tech tree...
